RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FIVE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 3 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHERNYAHOVSKIY rated just off the early speed while between rivals, was three wide on the second bend, fanned five wide for the stretch run and edged ahead of SUPER SILVEWR inside the final sixteenth. SUPER SILVER four wide on both turn, edged ahead upper stretch, lugged in briefly inside the final eighth then did not have enough left inside the last sixteenth. ZARMAE advanced from inside on the backstretch, did not keep up along the rail on the second bend, rallied in the lane, edged ahead for third nearing the sixteenth marker and just held his position. SOUPER FORTUNE broke on top, shared the lead while just off or along the rail, floated out some entering the stretch, slowly began to yield, was steadied briefly when SUPER SILVER came close inside the last furlong, continued to battle to keep third but lacked the extra needed in the waning yards. OVERTHOUGHT hesitated a bit at the break, quickly recovered to vie for the lead outside SOUPER FORTUNE but flattened out for the drive. CAMPAIGN SPY taken in hand behind traffic nearing the first turn, was a brief factor between rivals but soon faded once on the backstretch and had no late bid.

FERGIE ATTACK prominent just off the inside, retreated some along the rail on the turn, swung outside WICKED SKY for the stretch run, was all out, no match for the latter but easily best of the rest. SILVER EYES pressed from between rivals, did not keep up while two wide on the bend, fanned outside FERGIE ATTACK for the drive, lacked a rally but moved clear for third inside the last eighth. HOT N FRESH raced in contention from outside on the backstretch but faded two wide on the turn. MOLLY'S TEMPLE was sent to get the early lead between rivals, took the rail into the bend, was overtaken nearing the end of a half mile and steadily gave way. FEATURED POWER showed little in a ground-saving trip.

PACHI bumped leaving the chute, was boxed in behind rivals on the backstretch, just off the inside on the turn, swung out some for the stretch run and had no late bid. RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIL BIT TIPSEY inattentive in the gate, moved to the inside midway on the backstretch once the race began, angled outside KIANA'S LOVE entering the lane, was bumped by that one and forced out some nearing the eighth pole, moved clear approaching the final sixteenth, received slight urging the rest of the way and held sway. ROCK THE BIRDHOUSE also moved toward the inside midway on the backstretch, advanced two wide on the bend, was forced to angle out six wide at the top of the stretch, took over second inside the last sixteenth, came up short for the win but was clearly second best. KIANA'S LOVE gradually drifted out as she vied for the lead inside rivals once on the main track, moved clear of the others from just off the rail on the turn, was challenged in the lane, drifted out under left-handed pressure upper stretch, bumped LIL BIT TIPSEY, began to fade approaching the last sixteenth, was angled out at the sixteenth marker and continued to drift out further. WAR COLORS saved ground and only passed inside tires ones the final furlong. SMILE AT THE STORM contested the pace from outside horses on the backstretch, did not stay with KIANA'S LOVE on the turn, was forced out some by MY LADY SLEW at the top of the stretch and gave way. MY LADY SLEW displayed early speed between rivals, stayed in path three on the bend, was forced out some as LIL BIT TIPSEY squeezed through a narrow opening at the head of the lane and also gave way soon after.
